T* (BUILD ORDER) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Build the soprano C keyless version first. Do not add keywork until the) Tj
T* (bore, reed, and seven front holes speak reliably.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (PHASE 0 - DESIGN FREEZE) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. Pick the exact reed and mouthpiece.) Tj
T* (2. Print data/tone-hole-schedule.csv and mark which holes will be) Tj
T* (drilled in the first pass.) Tj
T* (3. Decide whether the prototype uses raised collars or plain chamfered) Tj
T* (holes. Plain holes tune faster; collars match the inspiration photo.) Tj
T* (4. Confirm the blank dimensions from cut-list.csv.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (PHASE 1 - BODY BLANK AND BORE) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. Mill/turn the blank oversize and mark the bore centerline.) Tj
T* (2. Drill the bore from the reed-seat end with the longest stable drill) Tj
T* (setup available.) Tj
T* (3. Ream or lap to final bore diameter. Measure at both ends.) Tj
T* (4. Turn the exterior body profile, leaving extra length at the bell end.) Tj
T* (5. Cut the mouthpiece socket/tenon but keep the reed setup removable.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (PHASE 2 - ROOT TUNING) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. Assemble reed, mouthpiece, and body with all holes undrilled.) Tj
T* (2. Measure the all-closed pitch.) Tj
T* (3. Trim the bell/foot in small steps only after the reed is stable.) Tj
T* (4. Record every trim amount in validation.csv.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (PHASE 3 - TONE HOLES) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. Lay out hole centers from data/tone-hole-schedule.csv, measuring) Tj
T* (from DATUM_BELL_FACE.) Tj
T* (2. Center punch lightly. A wandering bit will change tuning.) Tj
T* (3. Drill each hole 15-25 percent undersize.) Tj
T* (4. Open holes from low to high. After each enlargement, play the target) Tj
T* (note and log measured frequency.) Tj
T* (5. Chamfer only after pitch is close; chamfering can sharpen the note.) Tj
ET
